      <p><h4>About</h4> 

Dr Ila Patnaik serves as a professor at the National Institute of
      Public Finance and Policy, New Delhi. Prior to this, she was the
      Principal Economic Advisor to the Government of India. Her
      research interests include international macroeconomics, finance
      and emerging economy business cycles, with publications in
      scholarly journals such as the Journal of International Money
      and Finance, the World Bank Economic Review, International
      Finance, and in collected volumes. Dr Patnaik also served on
      various working groups and task forces of the Ministry of
      Finance.<br> <a href="bio.html">See full bio...</a>  </p>
    <p>
      <h4>Recent Publications</h4>
      <ul>
       <li>
          India Review:
          <a href="http://macrofinance.nipfp.org.in/releases/PP2016_India_growth_headed.html" target="_blank">Where is India's growth headed?</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          The World Bank Economic Review:<a href="http://macrofinance.nipfp.org.in/releases/PatnaikBhattacharya_financialInclusion_2015.html" target="_blank">
            Financial Inclusion, Productivity Shocks, and Consumption
            Volatility in Emerging Economies</a>
        </li>

        <li>
          Working paper, NIPFP: <a href="http://macrofinance.nipfp.org.in/releases/PPPS2016_cfm_motivations_effects.html" target="_blank">
            Motivations for Capital Controls and Their Effectiveness</a>
        </li>

        </ul>
